# Problem statement
The repo’s onboarding and operational documentation is inconsistent/outdated (README duplicates content, references missing docs), `env.example` is incomplete for first-time setup, and key “enterprise” UX/config behaviors are either hard-coded or inconsistent (e.g., story type slot counts, chain selection, AI tuning, NFT image theming).
# Current state (observed)
Documentation
* `README.md` contains duplicated sections and links to non-existent docs like `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md`, `docs/SECURITY.md`, etc.
* Story type info is inconsistent: contracts enforce Mini=10, Normal=20, Epic=35 slots (Epic owner-only), but parts of the UI/README still mention “Epic (200 slots)”.
Environment
* `env.example` is close, but is missing some variables used by scripts (`PRIVATE_KEY`, `KEYSTORE_PASSWORD`, etc.) and doesn’t document optional tuning knobs (AI generation params, NFT image theming, identity integrations).
AI + moderation
* Story generation is via `src/app/api/generate-story/route.ts` using `aiService` (OpenAI chat completions, model currently hard-coded).
* Word moderation is via `src/app/api/moderate-word/route.ts` using OpenAI Moderations directly; caching/fallback behavior is not centralized.
NFT rendering
* NFT image generation is in `src/app/api/nft/[tokenId]/image/route.ts` using pure SVG. There is no documented way to swap in background/template images.
App flow issues worth addressing
* Chain selection logic is inconsistent between client (`src/app/providers.tsx` uses `NODE_ENV`) and server routes (use `NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID`).
* User-facing “How to play” copy in `src/app/page.tsx` is inconsistent with contract reality (Epic slots).
* Client-side debug logging in `src/app/providers.tsx` is noisy for production.
# Proposed changes
## 1) Rewrite + de-duplicate README (dev quickstart + marketing + deployment)
* Replace `README.md` with a single canonical doc (no duplicated sections).
* Structure:
    * Dev Quickstart (clone → install → env → deploy contracts → run)
    * “What this is” marketing overview (features, differentiators)
    * Deployment (testnet + mainnet), plus required third-party services (RPC, AI, IPFS)
    * Visual repo tree (high-level) and key entry points
    * Links to deeper docs under `docs/`
    * Common pitfalls (signer mismatch, missing contract addrs, wrong chainId/RPC)
* Update story-spec language to match the intended product behavior:
    * Mini: ~50 total words in final story; 5–10 user slots
    * Normal: ~100 total words; 10–15 user slots
    * Epic (owner-only, rare): ~150 total words; 15–25 user slots
## 2) Create a real docs set under `docs/`
Create the docs referenced by the README:
* `docs/README.md` (documentation index)
* `docs/SETUP.md` (local dev + deployment flows)
* `docs/ENVIRONMENT.md` (all env vars explained + examples)
* `docs/AI.md` (AI story generation tuning, style control, and admin extra instructions)
* `docs/MODERATION.md` (word moderation behavior, fallbacks, and how to test)
* `docs/NFT_MEDIA.md` (metadata + image pipeline, and how to add background/template images)
* `docs/ADMIN.md` (admin dashboard + admin API routes)
Keep `docs/archive/` untouched.
## 3) Update `env.example` (required + optional) + embed quick-start
* Add missing deploy/script variables:
    * `PRIVATE_KEY` (or keystore path/password)
    * `KEYSTORE_PASSWORD` (local-only)
    * `COINMARKETCAP_API_KEY` (optional, gas reporter)
* Ensure all runtime vars used in `src/app/api/**` are present:
    * `STORY_TEMPLATE_SIGNER_PRIVATE_KEY`
    * `BASE_RPC_URL`, `BASE_SEPOLIA_RPC_URL`
* Add optional knobs (and document them) for:
    * AI story generation tuning (model, temperature, max tokens, timeout, global style append)
    * NFT background/template theming (both local `public/` and remote URLs, with fallback order)
    * Farcaster identity integration (optional; real lookups vs placeholder)
    * IPFS storage (optional; if you choose to host assets/metadata on IPFS)
* Include a concise “Quick start” comment block at the top.
## 4) Code changes required to support the updated story spec + enterprise configuration
### Story slot ranges (contract + client)
* Update `contracts/StoryManager.sol` to enforce slot COUNT RANGES instead of fixed values:
    * Mini: 5–10 slots
    * Normal: 10–15 slots
    * Epic: 15–25 slots (owner-only)
* Update tests in `test/GhostWriter.test.js` to use valid slot counts per type.
* Update frontend types + UI copy to reflect ranges.
### AI configuration (env + admin UI)
* Update `src/lib/ai-service.ts` to read env overrides:
    * `OPENAI_MODEL` (default `gpt-4o-mini`)
    * `OPENAI_TEMPERATURE` (default 0.9)
    * `OPENAI_MAX_TOKENS` (default 700)
    * `OPENAI_TIMEOUT_MS` (default 10000)
    * `AI_STORY_SYSTEM_PROMPT_APPEND` (optional)
* Update `src/components/admin-dashboard.tsx` to optionally expose these as advanced settings (write-only client-side fields that affect server behavior via env are not possible; so admin UI will call a new admin-only API to preview stories with overrides OR just manage “extra instructions” + show current env-derived values).
* Update story generation prompts to target:
    * Mini: ~50 words total, 5–10 placeholders
    * Normal: ~100 words total, 10–15 placeholders
    * Epic: ~150 words total, 15–25 placeholders
### Moderation consolidation
* Update `src/app/api/moderate-word/route.ts` to route through `aiService.moderateWord()` for consistent fallback + caching.
### NFT background/template images (local + remote)
* Update `src/app/api/nft/[tokenId]/image/route.ts` to optionally add a background layer:
    * Local backgrounds from `public/` (e.g. `/nft/backgrounds/adventure.png`)
    * Remote backgrounds (e.g. IPFS gateway / CDN)
    * Fallback order: local → remote → current gradient background
* Add env config for backgrounds (base URL + per-category mapping), documented in `docs/NFT_MEDIA.md`.
### UX consistency fixes
* Fix chain selection in `src/app/providers.tsx` to use `NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID` (align client with server routes).
* Fix user-facing story-type copy to remove incorrect slot counts.
* Gate noisy production logging.
## 5) App flow scan + scoped enterprise polish
Perform a focused pass on core flows:
* Connect wallet → browse stories → contribute → create story → view NFTs
* Admin dashboard: signer config, maxActiveStories, force complete, token buckets
Implement only high-signal improvements without redesign:
* consistent API error envelopes
* clearer UI when contracts/env aren’t configured
* remove incorrect copy and tighten loading states
